**************libpam module issue
ls /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/ | grep pam_faillock Replace pam.tally2.so with pam_faillock.so in below files sudo vim /etc/pam.d/common-auth
sudo vim /etc/pam.d/common-account ls /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/ | grep tally sudo rm /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/pam_tally*


**************libpam module issue
ls /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/ | grep pam_faillock 
Replace pam.tally2.so with pam_faillock.so in below files
sudo vim /etc/pam.d/common-auth
sudo vim /etc/pam.d/common-account 
ls /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/ | grep tally
sudo rm /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/security/pam_tally*
